text.tspan: Concerned personnel in Manning Office/ Manning Agent are responsible for the vessels under their charge and shall follow updiligently to ensure all flag certificates remain valid during the tenure of officers/ ratings contract period.4.16.3FLAG CERTIFICATIONFor flag Certification, below process shall be followed by concerned Manning Offices/ Manning Agents:Similar process will be followed when an officer or a ratings is promoted onboard or transferred from one vessel to the other.If the seafarer joining a vessel without the appropriate License/ Documents, the manning office should advise the master that theseafarer cannot undertake watch keeping duties until the flag administration has issued appropriate license and the document isonboard the vessel.4.17CREW TRAVELOn obtaining the schedule for departure from the port of disembarkation the following parties are to be notified by the TravelDepartment:a) The vesselâ€™s local agents at the port.b) The Master of the vessel.The Master is also to be notified of applicable deductions for the staff who have not completed their tour of duty.Operations and Travel department shall coordinate to ensure effective and economical crew changes are carried out as per attachedtravel process.If a crew member is signing off on medical grounds, travel department shall only arrange travel after confirming that "Fit to Travel" isstated in the medical report of the concerned crew member.4.18CREW HAND OVER
